JOHANNESBURG – The African National Congress (ANC) in Parliament has withdrawn its motion to nationalise the South African Reserve Bank (Sarb). The debate was scheduled to take place on Tuesday afternoon. The party in a tweet said it had done in order to consult further within party structures. The ANC in Parliament has withdrawn its motion “on full public ownership on the SARB in line with international practice” scheduled for debate this afternoon, to allow for greater consultation within structures of the African National Congress and key stakeholders. eNCA